parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to severe injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities
including hitting the steering wheel or dash
and failing to protect occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadvertent airbag deployment can cause unexpected and potentially dangerous situations, such as sudden stopping or loss of control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Airbags deploy unexpectedly
without a crash or impact
causing sudden stopping or loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctions in the airbag system can lead to delayed or incomplete deployment, which can reduce the effectiveness of the airbags in protecting occupants.
symptoms: Airbags deploy slowly or incompletely
or the dashboard cover appears melted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to perform recall repairs can lead to continued safety risks, including airbag failure to deploy.
symptoms: Recall repair not performed due to unavailability of parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to lock in the retracted position, making it impossible to use, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt sticks when trying to pull it down to buckle
the seat belt locks in the retracted position
the seat belt will not fully extend
the seat belt locks up multiple times when trying to pull it out to lock in place
the seat belt buckle fails to release
the seat belt jams up in the retracted position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to maneuver the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Heavy steering
loss of power assist
steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
steering wheel locks up
unusual noises while turning
sudden loss of steering control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause loss of control, especially at high speeds, which can lead to serious accidents.
symptoms: None reported
but the potential consequences of tie rod failure are severe.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Lubrication in Steering Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of lubrication in steering components can cause premature wear and failure, leading to loss of steering control and potential accidents.
symptoms: None reported
but the potential consequences of lack of lubrication are severe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering sensors can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to maneuver the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Sudden loss of steering control
feeling of driving on ice
no warning before loss of control.
